                "title": "Looking for Front End Developers",
                "link": "http://abraxastechnology.com/?p=322",
                "image": "",
                "pubDate": "Mon, 30 Nov -0001 00:00:00 +0000",
                "dcCreator": "Joshua Lawton",
                "guid": {
                    "-isPermaLink": "false",
                    "#text": "http://abraxastechnology.com/?p=322"
                },
                "contentEncoded": "In a town like Austin, with a slogan of “Keeping it Weird”, it’s hard to go anywhere that is not filled with creative people with an eye for design. That is, except when you come to our offices at Abraxas Technology. We love marketing, we love building products, and right now we are looking for a front end developer to come in and take the design ideas forward.  That’s where you come in. You love design. You love representing information in a way that is palatable, enjoyable, and easily understandable.  Lastly, you love a challenge and are looking for that opportunity to put your mark on a product by taking what backend developers and designers have done and building the front end. You have a portfolio of previous sites and products that you have either contributed to or built yourself.  If all of this applies to you, you might just be exactly the type of person we are looking for.  <strong>Responsibilities and Duties</strong> <ul>  	<li>Help form work conceptions</li>  	<li>Prototype concepts (software)</li>  	<li>Work in teams both internal (engineering) and external (marketing &amp; sales)</li>  	<li>Contribute to product specifications</li>  	<li>Take designs and create sustainable and manageable front ends.</li> </ul> <strong>Qualifications and Skills</strong> <ul>  	<li>Expertise in JavaScript, CSS, and HTML</li>  	<li>Experience with responsive design and backend technologies</li>  	<li>Advanced knowledge of HTML(5) and CSS(3)</li>  	<li>Experience with Bootstrap</li>  	<li>Strong knowledge of Angular.js, JavaScript, AJAX, jQuery, Web/Mobile responsive design</li>  	<li>Experience integrating front-end interactions using JavaScript and jQuery</li>  	<li>Experience integrating PHP with front-end code</li>  	<li>Experience with AJAX</li>  	<li>Expertise with WordPress including building custom functionality and themes</li>  	<li>Proficiency with Adobe Creative Suite and other industry software packages</li>  	<li>A strong work ethic (“9 to 5” is just a Dolly Parton song to you)</li>  	<li>You can think on your feet and adapt well to a quickly changing environment</li> </ul> Head on over to  <em>Abraxas Technology is committed to the principle of equal employment opportunity for all employees and to providing employees with a work environment free of discrimination and harassment. All employment decisions at Abraxas Technology are based on business needs, job requirements and individual qualifications, without regard to race, color, religion or belief, national, social or ethnic origin, sex (including pregnancy), age, physical, sexual orientation, gender identity, marital, civil union or domestic partnership status, past or present military service, family medical history or genetic information, family or parental status, or any other status protected by the laws or regulations in the locations where we operate. Abraxas Technology will not tolerate discrimination or harassment based on any of these characteristics.  </em>  &nbsp;",
